[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDuring a libFuzzer-driven test of `curl_fuzzer_http`, AddressSanitizer detected a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegmentation fault in the function `Curl_doh_close`. The fuzzer executed a single [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m times, triggering a wild-memory read when closing a DNS-over-HTTPS [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDoH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msession. The crash occurs at `[0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mdoh.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m1410:30[0m[39m`, and is reported as an [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer “SEGV on unknown address” with a high-value dereference. No [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfurther sanitizer diagnostics are available.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis issue arises when the fuzzing harness invokes `curl_fuzzer_http` under [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer with an input file [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The full sanitizer log shows:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * AddressSanitizer reports a deadly signal [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSEGV[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m caused by a read access to an [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid, high-value address.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * The crash site is in `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh.c line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating an attempt [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto dereference a corrupted or uninitialized pointer during teardown of a DoH [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msession.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * The stack trace leading to the crash is:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `Curl_doh_close` in lib/doh.c  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `Curl_req_done` in lib/request.c  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `multi_done` and `multi_runsingle` in lib/multi.c  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `curl_multi_perform` in lib/multi.c  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `fuzz_handle_transfer` in curl_fuzzer.cc  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in curl_fuzzer.cc  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m. Fuzzer driver routines in LLVM’s libFuzzer library  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * The fault is classified as a wild-addr-read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSCARINESS: [0m[1;36m20[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, suggesting a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer has been corrupted, freed, or never properly initialized before use.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * The failure consistently reproduces under the fuzzer with the provided [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtestcase.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * The harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`curl_fuzzer_http`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m simply feeds data into the normal curl multi [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minterface; it is not itself the root cause but triggers the underlying library bug.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * No further sanitizer hints [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., allocation stack[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are available in the log.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a complete understanding of this issue, investigation should focus on:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * The implementation of `Curl_doh_close` in `lib/doh.c` around line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentify what pointer or structure field may be invalid.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * The resource lifecycle for DoH sessions, including allocation, initialization, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand cleanup routines in `lib/doh.c`.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * The interaction between `Curl_req_done` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrequest completion[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `multi_done` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `lib/multi.c`, which ultimately calls the DoH cleanup.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * Any data structures or states manipulated by `fuzz_handle_transfer` in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer harness that drive the multi interface.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis crash represents a memory-safety vulnerability in Curl’s DoH handling code and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be reviewed to prevent out-of-bounds or use-after-free accesses.[0m             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:  return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1402[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1429[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1402[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1403[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1404[0m[39m:  struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1405[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh && data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1406[0m[39m:    struct Curl_easy *probe_data;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1407[0m[39m:    curl_off_t mid;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1408[0m[39m:    size_t slot;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1409[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mfor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mslot = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; slot < DOH_SLOT_COUNT; slot++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1410[0m[39m:      mid = doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1411[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmid < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1412[0m[39m:        continue;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1413[0m[39m:      doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1414[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* should have been called before data is removed from multi handle *[0m[35m/[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1415[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mDEBUGASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1416[0m[39m:      probe_data = data->multi ? [0m[1;35mCurl_multi_get_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, mid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m :[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1417[0m[39m:        NULL;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1418[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1419[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mDEBUGF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, [0m[32m"Curl_doh_close: xfer for [0m[32mmid[0m[32m=%"[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1420[0m[39m:                     FMT_OFF_T [0m[32m" not found!"[0m[39m,[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1421[0m[39m:                     doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1422[0m[39m:        continue;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1423[0m[39m:      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1424[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* data->multi might already be reset at this time *[0m[35m/[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1425[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mcurl_multi_remove_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1426[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mCurl_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1427[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1428[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1429[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash in Curl_doh_close is caused by dereferencing a dangling or [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muninitialized `data->req.doh` pointer.  After a DoH lookup completes, the code [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msometimes frees or resets the `doh` struct without clearing the pointer before [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalling Curl_req_done [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich unconditionally calls Curl_doh_close[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  This leaves [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` pointing at invalid memory, leading to a wild read.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Invariants to Preserve[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Respect existing request lifecycle: Soft reset [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCurl_req_soft_reset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m prepares [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor a new transfer, hard reset [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCurl_req_hard_reset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m clears most fields for a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconnection reuse, and full free [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCurl_req_free[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m tears down everything.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only change library code in `lib/request.c` and related cleanup routines [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_doh_close` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `Curl_doh_cleanup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure `data->req.doh` is never left [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdangling.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not touch fuzzing harness, multi logic, or external dependencies.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Strategy[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Unified DOH Cleanup on Request Completion[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `Curl_req_done` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlib/request.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, replace the call to [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` with `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Rationale: `Curl_doh_cleanup` invokes `Curl_doh_close` and then frees the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doh` struct and sets `data->req.doh` to NULL via `Curl_safefree`.  This guarantees[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno dangling pointer remains after a request completes.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Cleanup DOH State on Hard Reset[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `Curl_req_hard_reset` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlib/request.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, likewise replace [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` with `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Rationale: When the handle is reused via a hard reset, any leftover DOH [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstate must be torn down and pointer cleared to avoid stale references during the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnext request.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Defensive Cleanup on Soft Reset [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional but Recommended[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `Curl_req_soft_reset` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlib/request.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, insert immediately after the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_client_start[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor before any new DOH allocation[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m a block:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          #endif[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Rationale: Ensures that if any DOH state survived into a new transfer [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdue to early abort or error paths[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, it is cleaned up cleanly before new [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDNS-over-HTTPS probes are issued.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Step-by-Step Implementation[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Open `lib/request.c`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `CURLcode [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Locate:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #endif[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Change to:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #endif[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `void [0m[1;35mCurl_req_hard_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Locate:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #endif[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Change to:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #endif[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In `CURLcode [0m[1;35mCurl_req_soft_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` after `result = [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mCurl_client_start[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Insert:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #endif[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Using `Curl_doh_cleanup` rather than just closing the probes ensures the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstruct is freed and pointer nulled, preventing any future code path from [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereferencing a stale pointer.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing code paths that expect `data->req.doh` to be NULL when no DoH is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpending continue to work unchanged.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No modifications are made to the fuzzing harness, multi-perform logic, utility[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctions, or external libraries.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach mirrors other cleanup patterns in libcurl [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_req_free`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and follows the principle that resource teardown should null out [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointers after free.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigation[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removing the persistent `doh` struct earlier [0m[1;39m([0m[39mon request done or reset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot affect DoH lookup correctness because each DNS-over-HTTPS resolution is tied to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma single request lifecycle.  There is no intended reuse of the probe state across [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiple transfers.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additional calls to `Curl_doh_cleanup` on a NULL pointer are safe [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno-op via [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` guard[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Regression: existing tests for DOH will still see identical behavior: setup [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mruns probes, uses results, then cleanup removes probes and frees state.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Verification[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run AddressSanitizer-enabled fuzzing on `curl_fuzzer_http` to ensure [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegmentation faults in `Curl_doh_close` no longer occur.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing libcurl unit tests, especially DOH-related tests, to confirm no [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregressions.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure no memory leaks around DOH state via Valgrind/MSan as applicable.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` in `lib/doh.c` during fuzz testing of the HTTP fuzzer [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`curl_fuzzer_http`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The developer substituted calls to `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in two locations within `lib/request.c`, hoping to [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A libFuzzer-driven test [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`curl_fuzzer_http`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m running with AddressSanitizer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maborts with a SEGV on an apparently invalid [0m[1;39m([0m[39mhigh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m address read.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash originates in `Curl_doh_close` at `lib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410:30[0m[39m`.  [0m             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanitizer report labels the issue as “wild-addr-read” with SCARINESS [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations from the Initial Log  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The faulting instruction is within the DNS-over-HTTPS cleanup path [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_doh_close`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer is invoked with `-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m` on a single input; the crash reproduces[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistently.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No additional ASan diagnostics are printed beyond the raw invalid access.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `lib/request.c`, two instances of:  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This change was applied in the function handling request finalization and in a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecond cleanup block further down the same file.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After rebuilding and re-running, the crash still occurs; the new backtrace is:[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m13[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x563149285afd[0m[39m in _start [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/out/[0m[95mcurl_fuzzer_http+0x136afd[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: SEGV [0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mdoh.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m1410:30[0m[39m in Curl_doh_close[0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95madditional_issue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Notes[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatches if needed.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msingle patch attempt.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Try different approaches to resolve the issues.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Analysis [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Analysis Report[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Relevant Code Snippets[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_snippets>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1436[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1438[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1436[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1437[0m[39m:    data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1391[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1394[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1391[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* All done *[0m[35m/[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1392[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1393[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1394[0m[39m:    return result;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash arises because the DoH [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDNS-over-HTTPS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m state [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`data->req.doh`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtorn down twice:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Once prematurely in `Curl_doh_is_resolved` via `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreeing the `doh` context immediately after DNS resolution.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Again at transfer completion in `Curl_req_done`, either via [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39minitially[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or `Curl_doh_cleanup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter the first patch attempt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The premature cleanup invalidates internal pointers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDNS result slots, linked [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlists, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Later access in `Curl_doh_close` or inside the second invocation of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup thus leads to a wild-memory‐read.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Preservation of Critical Logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must still:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Call `[0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in `Curl_doh_is_resolved` to free temporary DNS‐entry[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing structures.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Delay the full DoH context teardown until the request is completely done [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_req_done`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must avoid touching fuzzer harness, multi‐handle logic, or any external [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPIs.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Strategy Outline[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Modify `Curl_doh_is_resolved` in `lib/doh.c`:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Remove the call to `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • This prevents premature destruction of the `data->req.doh` context [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately after name resolution.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Leave `[0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in place [0m[1;39m([0m[39mit only frees the local `de` struct[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. In the DoH‐cleanup path at transfer end [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_req_done` in `lib/request.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Restore cleanup to call exactly one function that performs full teardown.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Prefer `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich internally calls `Curl_doh_close` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand then frees the main `doh` struct[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and remove any direct calls to [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` here.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Verify that no other code path invokes `Curl_doh_cleanup` twice [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., do not[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall it from both the name‐resolution path and the completion path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Detailed Steps[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m – In `lib/doh.c`, locate the end of `Curl_doh_is_resolved` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Remove or comment out:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return result;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Replace it with:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* full DoH teardown deferred until Curl_req_done *[0m[35m/[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return result;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m – In `lib/request.c`, in both places where DoH cleanup is done [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthese [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere patched previously[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ensure they read:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       #endif[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Do not call `Curl_doh_close` directly anywhere in this file.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m – Ensure `Curl_doh_cleanup` is idempotent and safe when called once at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtransfer end:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • It should call `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` internally if needed, then free [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` and set it to NULL.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • Because the premature call was removed, no double‐free or dangling pointer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m – Add a regression‐test in the existing DoH test suite [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot in the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to validate that:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • Hostname resolution via DoH still works.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • The DoH context remains valid until `Curl_req_done` and is cleaned exactly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monce.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By removing the early cleanup in the name‐resolution path, we preserve the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min‐memory structures until the end of the transfer. This directly eliminates the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble‐free/dangling pointer that led to the wild-memory‐read in `Curl_doh_close`.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We maintain the existing cleanup-on-completion logic in `Curl_req_done` via [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_cleanup`, preserving current multi‐handle teardown behavior.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to harness, fuzzing code, or external libraries are required. [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExisting tests and fuzzer coverage will now complete the resolution and cleanup [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout crashing.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigation[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Side Effect: Memory used by the DoH context persists slightly longer [0m[1;39m([0m[39muntil [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequest end[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Mitigation: This is identical to non‐fuzzed code paths in typical HTTPS [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtransfers; memory overhead is minimal and transient.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Side Effect: If any other code path assumes the early cleanup, re‐verify all [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcallers of `Curl_doh_is_resolved`. It normally only signals DNS resolution status.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: Run the full DoH test suite, ensure no leaks beyond the expected [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtransfer‐end cleanup.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. References[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Analogous behavior in `lib/hostip.c` where name‐resolution contexts are freed [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly on handle cleanup, not within the resolution helper.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maintains the same use of `[0m[1;35mCurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_cleanup`, ensuring robust, single‐point teardown.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo further retrievals are necessary as this strategy directly addresses the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble‐cleanup root cause. [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer crash [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSEGV[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m occurs when fuzzing `curl_fuzzer_http`, triggered [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `Curl_doh_close` within `lib/doh.c`. The patch attempt defers full DoH teardown [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby commenting out a call to `Curl_doh_cleanup` in one path and replaces calls to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` with `Curl_doh_cleanup` in `request.c`. After applying the patch, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe fuzzer still crashes in `Curl_doh_close`, now invoked inside [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_cleanup`, indicating the issue persists.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer: `curl_fuzzer_http` invoked with libFuzzer, [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m runs on a single testcase.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Crash: AddressSanitizer reports a SEGV on READ of an invalid [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“high”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m address in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` at line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m of `lib/doh.c`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace highlights the sequence:  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mdoh.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m1410[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `Curl_req_done` [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mrequest.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m108[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `multi_done` → `multi_runsingle` → `curl_multi_perform` → fuzz harness in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`curl_fuzzer.cc` → libFuzzer runtime  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No additional sanitizer info; crash is reproducible in repeated runs.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The faulting address is invalid, suggesting use-after-free or uninitialized [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer in DoH cleanup code.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `Curl_req_done` unconditionally calls `Curl_doh_close` if DNS-over-HTTPS isn’t [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdisabled.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash happens before or during the deallocation steps in the DoH layer.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt and Post-patch Log  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `lib/doh.c`, the block that called `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` immediately after [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was replaced by a comment: “full DoH teardown deferred until [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCurl_req_done”.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `lib/request.c`, two calls to `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` were changed to [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After patch: fuzzer output still shows a SEGV at `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1410[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack now includes:  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mdoh.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m1410[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `Curl_doh_cleanup` [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mdoh.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m1435[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `Curl_req_done` [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mrequest.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m108[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. same multi/perform/fuzzer chain  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch did not prevent `Curl_doh_close` from being invoked [0m[1;39m([0m[39mit is called [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minside `Curl_doh_cleanup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so the underlying invalid memory access remains.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The internals of `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m in `lib/doh.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: pointer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidity, ownership, and lifecycle of DoH-specific data.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The interaction between `[0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `Curl_doh_*` functions—ensure no [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble-free or use-after-free of shared structures.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The distinction between `Curl_doh_cleanup` vs. `Curl_doh_close`: their [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresponsibilities and whether both should be called or only one.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sequence in `Curl_req_done` and `multi_done` to verify proper ordering of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup calls across the multi-handle state machine.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential missing initialization of DoH context or fields that could lead to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstale pointers in cleanup routines.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
