[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m127[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m128[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Can no longer [0m[1;35mmemset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m this struct as we need to keep some state *[0m[35m/[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo resolve the wild‐read crash in Curl_doh_close and eliminate the build‐breaking [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbrace error, we should [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m simplify and correct the guard in Curl_doh_close in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.c so it early-returns cleanly when no DoH state exists [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthus removing the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatched braces[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m move cleanup into request.c by calling Curl_doh_cleanup[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mwhich itself calls Curl_doh_close[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m only when data->req.doh is non-NULL. This both [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstops Curl_doh_close from being invoked with an invalid pointer and ensures full [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mteardown of DoH state in one place.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSteps:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Patch lib/doh.c**  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Remove the original `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh && data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block and replace it with [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma simple early-return guard:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* nothing to do if no DoH state or no multi handle *[0m[35m/[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!doh || !data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mfor[0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t slot = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; slot < DOH_SLOT_LAST; slot++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          curl_off_t mid = doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmid < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            continue;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mDEBUGASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          struct Curl_easy *probe_data =[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mCurl_multi_get_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, mid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mDEBUGF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata,[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[32m"Curl_doh_close: xfer for [0m[32mmid[0m[32m=%"[0m[39m FMT_OFF_T [0m[32m" not found!"[0m[39m,[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               mid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            continue;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mcurl_multi_remove_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. This removes the extraneous brace, restores balance, and ensures no read of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man uninitialized or freed `doh`.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Patch lib/request.c**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In both `Curl_req_done` and `Curl_req_hard_reset`, replace:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   with[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Rationale:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Curl_doh_cleanup` internally calls `Curl_doh_close`, frees header list [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`req_hds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and frees & NULLs `data->req.doh`.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A single guarded call to cleanup both removes remaining transfers and tears [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdown DoH state safely.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Calling cleanup only when `data->req.doh` is non-NULL prevents dereferencing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid pointers and avoids double-free.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Verify no other callers**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Grep for `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39m` to confirm only these sites [0m[1;39m([0m[39min request.c and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoh_cleanup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m invoke it. No changes needed elsewhere.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Justification**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The early-return in Curl_doh_close completely guards against null or invalid [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doh` or missing multi handle, preventing the AddressSanitizer crash.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consolidating “close + cleanup” into a single `Curl_doh_cleanup` call [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimplifies caller code, avoids redundant calls, and ensures header list and `doh` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstruct are freed exactly once.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removing the old if-block and its braces corrects the syntax error and allows [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe build to succeed.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach doesn’t touch harness, fuzzing macros, or external libraries; it[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserves existing functionality and test coverage.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Side-effect considerations**  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because `Curl_doh_cleanup` invokes `Curl_doh_close`, callers will no longer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanually call `Curl_doh_close` first; this is safe since cleanup always calls [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclose.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tests depending on `data->req.doh` being non-NULL until after cleanup must not[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minspect it post-cleanup; this is in line with existing lifecycle.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other protocol or utility code is modified, so risk is minimized.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Implementation notes**  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Use existing macros [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`DEBUGASSERT`, `infof`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and constants [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`DOH_SLOT_LAST`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FMT_OFF_T`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for consistency.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that `Curl_safefree` in `Curl_doh_cleanup` indeed sets `data->req.doh [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m= NULL`.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Build locally with ASan to verify no new sanitizer warnings.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run the `curl_fuzzer_http` target to ensure the fuzzer no longer crashes in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close`.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWith these changes, the build error is eliminated, and the segmentation fault in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCurl_doh_close is prevented by never invoking it when the DoH state is absent or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer crash was reported when running the HTTP fuzzer against curl’s [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDoH code. The fuzzer invocation triggered a segmentation fault in Curl_doh_close [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn in Curl_doh_close when no DoH state or no multi handle is present, [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplaced calls to Curl_doh_close in request.c with calls to Curl_doh_cleanup when [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata->req.doh is non-NULL, and [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m removed a redundant closing brace. After [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrebuilding and rerunning the fuzzer with the same input, the crash reoccurred in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCurl_doh_close [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow called from Curl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at nearly the same location.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer was invoked via `curl_fuzzer_http -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`, leading to an [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer report.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash happens inside Curl_doh_close [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mdoh.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m1410:30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m on a READ [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccess from a high [0m[1;39m([0m[39minvalid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m address.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace shows a sequence: Curl_doh_close → Curl_req_done → multi_done → [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti_runsingle → curl_multi_perform → fuzz_handle_transfer → [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLLVMFuzzerTestOneInput → FuzzerDriver → main.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe faulty function `Curl_doh_close`.[0m                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In lib/doh.c at line [0m[1;36m1402[0m[39m, an if-guard was inverted to return immediately when [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` is NULL or `data->multi` is NULL:  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```c[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!doh || !data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The original outer `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh && data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block’s closing brace was [0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1431[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1439[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1431[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1432[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1433[0m[39m:  struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1434[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1435[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1436[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1439[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:122[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m128[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m122[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mreq->sendbuf_init[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m123[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_bufq_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&req->sendbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m124[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m125[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m126[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m127[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m128[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Can no longer [0m[1;35mmemset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m this struct as we need to keep some state *[0m[35m/[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Root-cause confirmation**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash is a use-after-free in `Curl_doh_close`: after `Curl_doh_cleanup` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrees the `data->req.doh` struct, `data->req.doh` remains non-NULL, so a subsequent[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall to `Curl_doh_close` dereferences freed memory.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additionally, `Curl_req_done` and the “post-sendbuf” path in `request.c` still[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall `Curl_doh_close` directly, so a freed but non-NULL `data->req.doh` is hit [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtwice.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Primary fix – Nullify `data->req.doh` after cleanup**  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In `lib/doh.c`, modify `Curl_doh_cleanup` so that after freeing the `doh_probes`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstruct it sets `data->req.doh = NULL` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand clears the DoH bit in `data->conn`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;              [0m[35m/[0m[39m* remove handles safely *[0m[35m/[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* free header list *[0m[35m/[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* free the probes struct and avoid dangling pointer *[0m[35m/[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       data->req.doh = NULL;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->conn[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         data->conn->bits.doh = FALSE;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This prevents any later call to `Curl_doh_close` from seeing a stale pointer.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Replace all direct `Curl_doh_close` calls with conditional [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_cleanup`**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In `lib/request.c`, ensure *every* call site that used to do:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   is rewritten to:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Concretely:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In **`Curl_req_done`** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m108[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the “post-sendbuf” cleanup path [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m122[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m128[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or any other place [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` appears.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This guarantees no code path will call `Curl_doh_close` on a freed or NULL [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Guard against re-initialization of DoH state**  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In `lib/doh.c` at the start of `Curl_doh`, add:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* clean up any residual state before starting a new DoH resolution *[0m[35m/[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This ensures the easy handle’s `req.doh` is always freshly allocated, preventing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstale or double-freed structures.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Preserve existing functionality and API**  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do not alter any public API, harness, or fuzzing logic.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All changes are confined to the internal DoH cleanup and request teardown [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Conditional cleanup preserves the semantics of “remove outstanding DoH probes”[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexactly once per transfer.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Side-effects and mitigation**  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By clearing `data->conn->bits.doh`, we restore the connection’s DoH flag back [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto FALSE after cleanup, matching the initial state.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Conditional calls guarantee no double-close or double-free of the probes [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstruct.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The added guard in `Curl_doh` prevents silent leaks or inconsistent re-use [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout requiring DEBUGASSERTs in release builds.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Reapplying previous patches**  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The early-return guard in `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!doh || !data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is still valid and should be preserved.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The removal of stray braces around that block remains correct.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m. **Validation plan**  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild curl with the patched code, run the HTTP fuzzer for >[0m[1;36m1000[0m[39m iterations [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto verify no AddressSanitizer reports in `Curl_doh_close`.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run the full libcurl test suite to ensure no regressions.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that real DoH-based name lookups still succeed and clean up properly.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis comprehensive strategy addresses the dangling pointer root cause, ensures [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midempotent cleanup, avoids wild memory reads, and preserves existing logic and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
